Employee Management Program
The Employee Management Program is a dynamic linked list implementation in C programming, designed to help companies keep their employee records organized. The program provides a user-friendly, menu-driven interface allowing users to perform basic tasks on employee data, such as adding an employee to the current linked list, displaying employee data, searching employees based on specific criteria, and more.

Features
The program offers the following menu options:

Add a new employee
Print data of all employees
Print data of the nth employee
Search for employee based on empId
Search for employee based on full name
Count the total number of employees
Sort the employees based on their empId
Remove the nth employee in the current LL
Remove all employees in the current LL
Exit
After each menu option is executed (except for the Exit option), the user is brought back to the menu and re-prompted to enter a new command.

Folder Structure
The repository contains the following folders:

src: Contains all source files
include: Contains the header file headerA3.h
bin: Contains the executable file proFile
How to Run
To run the program, execute the following command:

bash
Copy code
./bin/proFile
Disclaimer
This program is designed for educational purposes and is not intended for use in production environments. Please use it responsibly and ensure proper data handling and security measures are implemented for any commercial applications.
